summary: This document appears to be a pre-trial preparation note for an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA), detailing a witness's previously undisclosed or clarified recollections regarding payments for photographs and massages involving Jeffrey Epstein. It is subject to a protective order.

connections.description: MI paid witness I for photographs taken.
Jeffrey Epstein paid witness I for massages, with amounts up to $500 mentioned.
Jeffrey Epstein invited El to join him for showers or steam before massages.

events.title: Witness Testimony Preparation
events.description: Preparation of a witness's testimony regarding payments for photographs and massages involving Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: A witness ('I') does not remember exactly how much she was paid when 'MI' took photos of her.
The witness thought 'MI' looked between 28 and 34 years old.
Jeffrey Epstein (JE) would shower or steam before massages and sometimes invited 'El' to join him.
The witness believes she received up to $500 for some massages.
The document is subject to a protective order covering specific paragraphs (7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17).
